I"Ã<p>Use IR receiver <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">TSOP4838</code> and Arduino to receive remote controller IR codes. Start monitoring the serial console, and then press the remote controller button.</p>

<p>Only <a href="https://github.com/cyborg5/IRLib2/blob/master/IRLibProtocols/IRLibProtocols.h#L15-L29">supported protocols for the remote controllers</a> can be used. If the protocol is supported, then the serial consoleâ€™s first line will show the decoded protocol and the hex code values.</p>

<h3 id="debugging">Debugging</h3>

<p>For error on <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">lto1: internal compiler error: in lto_output_varpool_node, at lto-cgraph.c:624</code>, install version <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">1.6.21</code> of the <a href="https://github.com/cyborg5/IRLib2">IR Arduino library</a>:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>arduino-cli core install arduino:avr@1.6.21
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="sample-remote-control-hex">Sample Remote control HEX</h2>

<p>For Benq projector remote control</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>ON
Decoded NEC(1): Value:CF20D

OFF
Decoded NEC(1): Value:C728D

Increase volume
Decoded NEC(1): Value:C41BE

Decrease volume
Decoded NEC(1): Value:CC13E

Eco blank
Decoded NEC(1): Value:CE01F
</code></pre></div></div>
